arts.ttl: Leyton Orient 0 Exeter City 1 - Grecians grind out battling away win - Devon Live
arts.sum: Orient missed a hatful of chances in the second half to draw level, the best of them seeing Brandon Cooper seeing a header from close range kept out by Joe Whitworth, who then made an incredible save from Charlie Kelman as the hosts pushed for an equalizer. Exeter City: (3-4-3) Joe Whitworth, Pierce Sweeney, Tristan Crama, Johnly Yfeko, Jack McMillan, Ryan Woods, Ed Francis (Mustapha Carayol, 83), Ilmari Niskanen, Amani Richards (Millenic Alli, 60), Kamari Doyle (Caleb Watts, 73), Josh Magennis (Sonny Cox, 83)

arts.ttl: Joe Whitworth stars again as Exeter City loanees prove vital
arts.sum: The Leicester City loanee was the Fox in the box to poke home from close range after Josh Magennis’ knockdown – and ultimately that was the vital goal as City extended their unbeaten run and rose to tenth. Exeter City manager Gary Caldwell heaped praise on goalkeeper Joe Whitworth after his side celebrated a 1-0 win at Leyton Orient.

arts.ttl: Amani Richards fires Exeter to victory at Leyton Orient
Exeter City want to make good point a brilliant one and grab all three at Leyton Orient
arts.sum: A point from the goalless draw at Wigan Athletic on Saturday was not to be sniffed at, but Gary Caldwell still wants more from his players ahead of Exeter City’s trip to Leyton Orient tonight. The Grecians will clock up just short of 1,000 miles on the road for these back-to-back away games at Wigan and Orient, which gives Caldwell and his players little time to work on things in training.

arts.ttl: Exeter City valuable point becomes brilliant - if they win on Tuesday - Devon Live
arts.sum: Exeter City manager Gary Caldwell said that Grecians’ point away to Wigan Athletic will prove to be a brilliant one – if they can claim all three points at Leyton Orient on Tuesday night. "I think it will prove to be a positive point if we go on to win our next game on Tuesday,” Caldwell said.

arts.ttl: Exeter City Women exit League Cup after defeat to Ipswich Town
arts.sum: The visitors started the second period strongly, Jess Sandland blocking a low cross before an effort on the turn drifted wide of Giles’ goal. Giles was alert to stop an Isabella Fisher drive in the opening minute, City’s backline caught from a long ball as the visitors started brightly.
